content:
Use the unique ID assigned to each synchronization operation to improve your debugging and troubleshooting experience. With the sync ID appended to the logs, you can easily filter and trace sync transactions and plan necessary actions.

This change applies to Lightning Experience in Enterprise and Unlimited editions where Consumer Goods Cloud is enabled.

When a sales rep encounters a sync error on their mobile device, the unique sync ID in the error message helps the admin troubleshoot the issue better. The admin uses the sync ID to identify the relevant log records from the device logs and Salesforce logs and provide the appropriate resolution.

From the App Launcher, find and select Sync Configuration. Click Sync Settings. In the General Settings section, select the Include sync ID in logs checkbox. This setting is enabled by default.
title: Improving Sync Debugging with Sync IDs
